Package generics

Class Collection<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • generics.Collection<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The placeholder for the actual type that will be determined when a Collection is created.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    MinMax<T>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DoubleCollection, IntegerCollection
    abstract class Collection<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
extends java.lang.Object
implements MinMax<T>
    This is the abstract Collection class that implements the generic interface MinMax.

    This class provides methods for collections(arrays) of comparable types. It provides non-type-specific methods for calculating the minimum and maximum values in the collections.

    The extending classes must provide their own implementation for the abstract method printCollection() however.

    NOTE: Because this class is abstract, and non-generic classes require an explicit type to be invoked, the extending classes specify the type used within them.

    Collections of type Double are created using DoubleCollection and collections of type Integer are created using IntegerCollection.

    Author:
    Dalton

      • min

        public T min()
        Generic method in MinMax interface

        This method finds and returns the minimum value found in a given set of objects.

        NOTE: Due to the generic method being in MinMax, a type for T did not need to be defined. This allows the method to be used in IntegerCollection and DoubleCollection without creating new methods in those classes.

        This demonstrates code reuse.

        Specified by:
